dcterms:title: AgentAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: AgentAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for a related Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: AgentAgentRole
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary for the roles appropriate to the class of resource an AgentRole is related to.

dcterms:title: AgentAgentRole
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: AgentAgentRole
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for agentRole is given.

dcterms:title: AgentAgentRole
skos:description: The numerical position of an AgentRole in a set of AgentRoles that have the same combination of agentRole, agentRoleIRI, agentRoleVocabulary and related target.
skos:note: One could use agentRoleOrder to create an ordered list of collectors (agentRole = 'collector') for a dwc:MaterialEntity, for example. The first would have agentRoleOrder=1, the second would have agentRoleOrder=2.

dcterms:title: AgentAgentRole
skos:description: The interval during which an AgentRole was in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: AgentIdentifier
skos:description: An unambiguous reference to a resource within a given context.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to identify a resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.

dcterms:title: AgentIdentifier
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: AgentIdentifier
skos:description: The category or system that best matches the nature of an Identifier.

dcterms:title: AgentIdentifier
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Identifier.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: AgentIdentifier
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in identifierType is given.

dcterms:title: AgentIdentifier
skos:description: A language in which an Identifier is presented.
skos:note: Recommended best prectice is to use an ISO639-2 three-letter language code.

dcterms:title: AgentMedia
skos:description: An identifier for a Media instance.

dcterms:title: AgentMedia
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: AgentMedia
skos:description: A term to describe the content of the image by a value from a controlled vocabulary.
skos:note: Controlled vocabulary of subjects to support broad classification of media items. Terms from various controlled vocabularies may be used. AC-recommended vocabularies are preferred and MAY be unqualified literals (not a full URI). For terms from other vocabularies either a precise URI SHOULD be used, or, as long as all unqualified terms in all vocabularies are unique, metadata SHOULD provide the source vocabularies using the Subject Category Vocabulary term. The value SHOULD be a string, whose text can also be in the form of a URL. These guidelines on value format are less restrictive than is specified by the IPTC guidelines.

dcterms:title: AgentMedia
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the subject category of the Media instance.

dcterms:title: AgentMedia
skos:description: Any vocabulary or formal classification from which terms in the Subject Category have been drawn.
skos:note: The AC recommended vocabularies do not need to be cited here. There is no required linkage between individual Subject Category terms and the vocabulary; the mechanism is intended to support discovery of the normative URI for a term, but not guarantee it.

dcterms:title: Agent
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Agent
skos:description: The category that best matches the type of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Agent
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Agent
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in agentType is given.

dcterms:title: Agent
skos:description: The name of an Agent preferred in searches and results.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAgentRole

skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for agentRole is given.

skos:description: The numerical position of an AgentRole in a set of AgentRoles that have the same combination of agentRole, agentRoleIRI, agentRoleVocabulary and related target.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: An identifier a chrono:ChronometricAge.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of an Assertion.
skos:example: `mass`; `mean mass`; `weight standard deviation`; `minimum organism quantity`; `water temperature`; `salinity`

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for assertionType is given.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: The date on which an Assertion was created.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: The date on which the state or measurement of an Assertion was deemed to first be in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is not numeric.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the value of an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for assertionValue is given.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is numeric.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: The units associated with the value in assertionValueNumeric.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Ontology of Units of Measure http://www.wurvoc.org/vocabularies/om-1.8/ of SI units, derived units, or other non-SI units accepted for use within the SI. For units that are composed of multiple parts, use the patterns as given in "A Primer for Communicating Mathematics via Plain Text" (https://cse.sc.edu/~fenner/latex-ASCII.pdf) by Stephen Fenner (e.g., `g/cm^3` for grams per cubic centimeter). For other units, provide the value as a recognizable standard (e.g., '%') or written out in full and in the plural (e.g., `individuals`). It is fine to provide non-SI units in the original language of the dataset.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: The IRI for the units of an assertionValueNumeric.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionUnit is given.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who made an Assertion.
skos:example: `José E. Crespo`; `Oliver P. Pearson | Anita K. Pearson`, `FMNH`

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent who made an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.
skos:example: `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097` (for an individual); `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097 | https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0098` (for a list of people)

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: The names of, references to, or descriptions of the methods or protocols used in making an Assertion.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for a Protocol used to make an Assertion.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/322/5899/261`; `Christopher J. Conroy, Jennifer L. Neuwald. 2008. Phylogeographic study of the California vole, Microtus californicus Journal of Mammalogy, 89(3):755-767.`; `Steven R. Hoofer and Ronald A. Van Den Bussche. 2001. Phylogenetic Relationships of Plecotine Bats and Allies Based on Mitochondrial Ribosomal Sequences. Journal of Mammalogy 82(1):131-137. | Walker, Faith M., Jeffrey T. Foster, Kevin P. Drees, Carol L. Chambers. 2014. Spotted bat (Euderma maculatum) microsatellite discovery using illumina sequencing. Conservation Genetics Resources.`

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeAssertion
skos:description: Comments or notes about an Assertion.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: An identifier for a Citation.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: An identifier a chrono:ChronometricAge.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a Citation.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Citation.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in citationType is given.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: A bibliographic reference for the resource.
skos:note: From Dublin Core, 'Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.' The intended usage of this term in Darwin Core is to provide the preferred way to cite the resource itself. Note that the intended usage of dcterms:references in Darwin Core, by contrast, is to point to the definitive source representation of the resource, if one is available.
skos:example: `Museum of Vertebrate Zoology, UC Berkeley. MVZ Mammal Collection (Arctos). Record ID: http://arctos.database.museum/guid/MVZ:Mamm:165861?seid=101356. Source: http://ipt.vertnet.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=mvz_mammal.` (Occurrence example); `https://www.gbif.org/species/2439608 Source: GBIF Taxonomic Backbone` (Taxon example); `Rand, K.M., Logerwell, E.A. The first demersal trawl survey of benthic fish and invertebrates in the Beaufort Sea since the late 1970s. Polar Biol 34, 475–488 (2011). https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-010-0900-2` (Event example)

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: The number of the page on which the citation occurs in the cited reference.
skos:note: From Dublin Core, 'Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.' The intended usage of this term in Darwin Core is to provide the preferred way to cite the resource itself. Note that the intended usage of dcterms:references in Darwin Core, by contrast, is to point to the definitive source representation of the resource, if one is available.
skos:example: `Museum of Vertebrate Zoology, UC Berkeley. MVZ Mammal Collection (Arctos). Record ID: http://arctos.database.museum/guid/MVZ:Mamm:165861?seid=101356. Source: http://ipt.vertnet.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=mvz_mammal.` (Occurrence example); `https://www.gbif.org/species/2439608 Source: GBIF Taxonomic Backbone` (Taxon example); `Rand, K.M., Logerwell, E.A. The first demersal trawl survey of benthic fish and invertebrates in the Beaufort Sea since the late 1970s. Polar Biol 34, 475–488 (2011). https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-010-0900-2` (Event example)

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: An identifier for the reference in which a Citation occurs.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a reference.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of reference.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in referenceType is given.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: The year the reference in a Citation was published.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: An indication of whether the reference for a Citation was peer reviewed.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeCitation
skos:description: Comments or notes about a Citation.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeMedia
skos:description: An identifier for a Media instance.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeMedia

skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeMedia
skos:description: A term to describe the content of the image by a value from a controlled vocabulary.
skos:note: Controlled vocabulary of subjects to support broad classification of media items. Terms from various controlled vocabularies may be used. AC-recommended vocabularies are preferred and MAY be unqualified literals (not a full URI). For terms from other vocabularies either a precise URI SHOULD be used, or, as long as all unqualified terms in all vocabularies are unique, metadata SHOULD provide the source vocabularies using the Subject Category Vocabulary term. The value SHOULD be a string, whose text can also be in the form of a URL. These guidelines on value format are less restrictive than is specified by the IPTC guidelines.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeProtocol
skos:description: An identifier for a Protocol.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAgeProtocol
skos:description: An identifier a chrono:ChronometricAge.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: An identifier for a chrono:ChronometricAge.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The verbatim age for a dwc:Event, whether reported by a dating assay, associated references, or legacy information.
skos:note: For example, this could be the radiocarbon age as given in an AMS dating report. This could also be simply what is reported as the age of a specimen in legacy collections data.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: A description of or reference to the methods used to determine a chrono:ChronometricAge.
skos:example: `radiocarbon AMS`; `K-Ar dates for the lower most marker tuff`; `historic documentation`; `ceramic seriation`

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: An identifier for the Protocol used to determine a ChronometricAge.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The output of a dating assay before it is calibrated into an age using a specific conversion protocol.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The method used for converting the chrono:uncalibratedChronometricAge into a chronometric age in years, as captured in the chrono:earliestChronometricAge, chrono:earliestChronometricAgeReferenceSystem, chrono:latestChronometricAge, and chrono:latestChronometricAgeReferenceSystem fields.
skos:note: For example, calibration of conventional radiocarbon age or the currently accepted age range of a cultural or geological period.
skos:example: `INTCAL13`; `sequential 6 phase Bayesian model and IntCal13 calibration`

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: An identifier for the Protocol used to convert a chrono:uncalibratedChronometricAge into a chronometric age in years, as captured in the chrono:earliestChronometricAge, chrono:earliestChronometricAgeReferenceSystem, chrono:latestChronometricAge, and chrono:latestChronometricAgeReferenceSystem fields.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The maximum/earliest/oldest possible age of a specimen as determined by a dating method.
skos:note: The expected unit for this field is years. This field, if populated, must have an associated chrono:earliestChronometricAgeReferenceSystem.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The reference system associated with the chrono:earliestChronometricAge.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The minimum/latest/youngest possible age of a specimen as determined by a dating method.
skos:note: The expected unit for this field is years. This field, if populated, must have an associated latestChronometricAgeReferenceSystem.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The reference system associated with the chrono:latestChronometricAge.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The temporal uncertainty of the chrono:earliestChronometricAge and chrono:latestChronometicAge in years.
skos:note: The expected unit for this field is years. The value in this field is number of years before and after the values given in the earliest and latest chronometric age fields within which the actual values are estimated to be.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The method used to generate the value of chrono:ChronometricAgeUncertaintyInYears.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: A description of the material on which the chrono:ChronometricAgeProtocol was actually performed, if known.
skos:example: `Double Tuff`; `Charcoal found in Stratum V`; `charred wood`; `tooth`

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: An identifier for the MaterialEntity on which the chrono:ChronometricAgeProtocol was performed, if applicable.

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The relationship of the chrono:materialDated to a dwc:MaterialEntity, from which the chrono:ChronometricAge of the related dwc:MaterialEntity and any related dwc:Occurrence is inferred.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.
skos:example: `sameAs` (cases where the subject material was completely destructively subsampled to get the chrono:ChronometricAge); `subsampleOf` (cases where part of the original MaterialEntity was extracted as the material used to determine the chrono:ChronometricAge); `inContextWith` (cases where the chrono:ChronometricAge is inferred from materialDated, such as sediments or cultural objects, in related temporal context); `stratigraphicallyCorrelatedWith` (cases where the chrono:ChronometricAge is inferred from materialDated in a stratigraphically correlated context)

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who determined the chrono:ChronometricAge.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space ( | ).

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The identifier for the Agent who determined the chrono:ChronometricAge.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to provide a single identifier that disambiguates the details of the acting agent. If a list is used, the order of the agents on the list should not be assumed to convey any semantics. Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: The date on which the chrono:ChronometricAge was determined.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.
skos:example: `1963-03-08T14:07-0600` (8 Mar 1963 at 2:07pm in the time zone six hours earlier than UTC); `2009-02-20T08:40Z` (20 February 2009 8:40am UTC); `2018-08-29T15:19` (3:19pm local time on 29 August 2018); `1809-02-12` (some time during 12 February 1809); `1906-06` (some time in June 1906); `1971` (some time in the year 1971).

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with the chrono:ChronometricAge.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space ( | ).
skos:example: `Pluckhahn, Thomas J., Neill J. Wallis, and Victor D. Thompson. 2020 The History and Future of Migrationist Explanation in the Archaeology of the Eastern Woodlands: A Review and Case Study of the Woodland Period Gulf Coast. Journal of Archaeological Research. https://doi.org/10.1007/s10814-019-09140-x`

dcterms:title: ChronometricAge
skos:description: Comments or notes about a chrono:ChronometricAge.
skos:example: `Beta Analytic number: 323913 | One of the Crassostrea virginica right valve specimens from North Midden Feature 17 was chosen for AMS dating, but it is unclear exactly which specimen it was.`

dcterms:title: CollectionAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

skos:note: For physical specimens, the recommended best practice is to use a globally unique and resolvable identifier from a collections registry such as the GBIF Registry of Scientific Collections (https://www.gbif.org/grscicoll).

skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the role of an Agent.

skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for agentRole is given.

dcterms:title: CollectionAssertion

dcterms:title: CollectionAssertion
skos:description: The units associated with the value in assertionValueNumeric.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Ontology of Units of Measure http://www.wurvoc.org/vocabularies/om-1.8/ of SI units, derived units, or other non-SI units accepted for use within the SI. For units that are composed of multiple parts, use the patterns as given in "A Primer for Communicating Mathematics via Plain Text" (https://cse.sc.edu/~fenner/latex-ASCII.pdf) by Stephen Fenner (e.g., `g/cm^3` for grams per cubic centimeter). skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionUnit is given.

dcterms:title: CollectionAssertion

skos:description: An identifier for an Agent who made an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.
skos:example: `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097` (for an individual); `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097 | https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0098` (for a list of people)

dcterms:title: CollectionAssertion
skos:description: The names of, references to, or descriptions of the methods or protocols used in making an Assertion.

dcterms:title: CollectionAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for a Protocol used to make an Assertion.

dcterms:title: CollectionAssertion
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/322/5899/261`; `Christopher J. Conroy, Jennifer L. Neuwald. 2008. Phylogeographic study of the California vole, Microtus californicus Journal of Mammalogy, 89(3):755-767.`; `Steven R. Hoofer and Ronald A. Van Den Bussche. 2001. Phylogenetic Relationships of Plecotine Bats and Allies Based on Mitochondrial Ribosomal Sequences. Journal of Mammalogy 82(1):131-137. | Walker, Faith M., Jeffrey T. Foster, Kevin P. Drees, Carol L. Chambers. 2014. Spotted bat (Euderma maculatum) microsatellite discovery using illumina sequencing. Conservation Genetics Resources.`

dcterms:title: CollectionAssertion
skos:description: Comments or notes about an Assertion.

dcterms:title: CollectionMedia
skos:description: An identifier for a Media instance.

dcterms:title: CollectionMedia
skos:description: An identifier for a Collection.
skos:note: For physical specimens, the recommended best practice is to use a globally unique and resolvable identifier from a collections registry such as the GBIF Registry of Scientific Collections (https://www.gbif.org/grscicoll).

dcterms:title: CollectionMedia
skos:description: A term to describe the content of the image by a value from a controlled vocabulary.
skos:note: Controlled vocabulary of subjects to support broad classification of media items. Terms from various controlled vocabularies may be used. AC-recommended vocabularies are preferred and MAY be unqualified literals (not a full URI). For terms from other vocabularies either a precise URI SHOULD be used, or, as long as all unqualified terms in all vocabularies are unique, metadata SHOULD provide the source vocabularies using the Subject Category Vocabulary term. The value SHOULD be a string, whose text can also be in the form of a URL. These guidelines on value format are less restrictive than is specified by the IPTC guidelines.

dcterms:title: CollectionMedia
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the subject category of the Media instance.

dcterms:title: CollectionMedia
skos:description: Any vocabulary or formal classification from which terms in the Subject Category have been drawn.
skos:note: The AC recommended vocabularies do not need to be cited here. There is no required linkage between individual Subject Category terms and the vocabulary; the mechanism is intended to support discovery of the normative URI for a term, but not guarantee it.

dcterms:title: Collection
skos:description: An identifier for a Collection.
skos:note: For physical specimens, the recommended best practice is to use a globally unique and resolvable identifier from a collections registry such as the GBIF Registry of Scientific Collections (https://www.gbif.org/grscicoll).

dcterms:title: Collection
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a Collection.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Collection
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Collection.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Collection
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in collectionType is given.

dcterms:title: Collection
skos:description: The name of a Collection.

dcterms:title: Collection
skos:description: The name, acronym, coden, or initialism identifying a Collection.

dcterms:title: Collection
skos:description: The identifier for an institution.
skos:note: For physical specimens, the recommended best practice is to use a globally unique and resolvable identifier from a collections registry such as the Research Organization Registry (ROR) or the GBIF Registry of Scientific Collections (https://www.gbif.org/grscicoll).

dcterms:title: Collection
skos:description: The name of an institution or organization.

dcterms:title: Collection
skos:description: The name (or acronym) in use by an institution.

dcterms:title: EventAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: EventAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: EventAgentRole
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary for the roles appropriate to the class of resource an AgentRole is related to.

dcterms:title: EventAgentRole
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: EventAgentRole
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for agentRole is given.

dcterms:title: EventAgentRole
skos:description: The numerical position of an AgentRole in a set of AgentRoles that have the same combination of agentRoleTargetID and agentRoleTargetType.
skos:note: One could use agentRoleOrder to create an ordered list of collectors for a dwc:MaterialEntity, for example. The first would have agentRoleOrder=1, the second would have agentRoleOrder=2.

dcterms:title: EventAgentRole
skos:description: The interval during which an AgentRole was in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of an Assertion.
skos:example: `mass`; `mean mass`; `weight standard deviation`; `minimum organism quantity`; `water temperature`; `salinity`

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for assertionType is given.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: The date on which an Assertion was created.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: The date on which the state or measurement of an Assertion was deemed to first be in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is not numeric.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the value of an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for assertionValue is given.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is numeric.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: The units associated with the value in assertionValueNumeric.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Ontology of Units of Measure http://www.wurvoc.org/vocabularies/om-1.8/ of SI units, derived units, or other non-SI units accepted for use within the SI. For units that are composed of multiple parts, use the patterns as given in "A Primer for Communicating Mathematics via Plain Text" (https://cse.sc.edu/~fenner/latex-ASCII.pdf) by Stephen Fenner (e.g., `g/cm^3` for grams per cubic centimeter). For other units, provide the value as a recognizable standard (e.g., '%') or written out in full and in the plural (e.g., `individuals`). It is fine to provide non-SI units in the original language of the dataset.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: The IRI for the units of an assertionValueNumeric.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionUnit is given.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who made an Assertion.
skos:example: `José E. Crespo`; `Oliver P. Pearson | Anita K. Pearson`, `FMNH`

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent who made an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.
skos:example: `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097` (for an individual); `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097 | https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0098` (for a list of people)

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: The names of, references to, or descriptions of the methods or protocols used in making an Assertion.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for a Protocol used to make an Assertion.

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/322/5899/261`; `Christopher J. Conroy, Jennifer L. Neuwald. 2008. Phylogeographic study of the California vole, Microtus californicus Journal of Mammalogy, 89(3):755-767.`; `Steven R. Hoofer and Ronald A. Van Den Bussche. 2001. Phylogenetic Relationships of Plecotine Bats and Allies Based on Mitochondrial Ribosomal Sequences. Journal of Mammalogy 82(1):131-137. | Walker, Faith M., Jeffrey T. Foster, Kevin P. Drees, Carol L. Chambers. 2014. Spotted bat (Euderma maculatum) microsatellite discovery using illumina sequencing. Conservation Genetics Resources.`

dcterms:title: EventAssertion
skos:description: Comments or notes about an Assertion.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: An identifier for a Citation.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a Citation.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Citation.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in citationType is given.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: A bibliographic reference for the resource.
skos:note: From Dublin Core, 'Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.' The intended usage of this term in Darwin Core is to provide the preferred way to cite the resource itself. Note that the intended usage of dcterms:references in Darwin Core, by contrast, is to point to the definitive source representation of the resource, if one is available.
skos:example: `Museum of Vertebrate Zoology, UC Berkeley. MVZ Mammal Collection (Arctos). Record ID: http://arctos.database.museum/guid/MVZ:Mamm:165861?seid=101356. Source: http://ipt.vertnet.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=mvz_mammal.` (Occurrence example); `https://www.gbif.org/species/2439608 Source: GBIF Taxonomic Backbone` (Taxon example); `Rand, K.M., Logerwell, E.A. The first demersal trawl survey of benthic fish and invertebrates in the Beaufort Sea since the late 1970s. Polar Biol 34, 475–488 (2011). https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-010-0900-2` (Event example)

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: The number of the page on which the citation occurs in the cited reference.
skos:note: From Dublin Core, 'Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.' The intended usage of this term in Darwin Core is to provide the preferred way to cite the resource itself. Note that the intended usage of dcterms:references in Darwin Core, by contrast, is to point to the definitive source representation of the resource, if one is available.
skos:example: `Museum of Vertebrate Zoology, UC Berkeley. MVZ Mammal Collection (Arctos). Record ID: http://arctos.database.museum/guid/MVZ:Mamm:165861?seid=101356. Source: http://ipt.vertnet.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=mvz_mammal.` (Occurrence example); `https://www.gbif.org/species/2439608 Source: GBIF Taxonomic Backbone` (Taxon example); `Rand, K.M., Logerwell, E.A. The first demersal trawl survey of benthic fish and invertebrates in the Beaufort Sea since the late 1970s. Polar Biol 34, 475–488 (2011). https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-010-0900-2` (Event example)

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: An identifier for the reference in which a Citation occurs.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a reference.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of reference.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in referenceType is given.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: The year the reference in a Citation was published.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: An indication of whether the reference for a Citation was peer reviewed.

dcterms:title: EventCitation
skos:description: Comments or notes about a Citation.

dcterms:title: EventIdentifier
skos:description: An unambiguous reference to a resource within a given context.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to identify a resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.

dcterms:title: EventIdentifier
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: EventIdentifier
skos:description: The category or system that best matches the nature of an Identifier.

dcterms:title: EventIdentifier
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Identifier.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: EventIdentifier
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in identifierType is given.

dcterms:title: EventIdentifier
skos:description: A language in which an Identifier is presented.
skos:note: Recommended best prectice is to use an ISO639-2 three-letter language code.

dcterms:title: EventMedia
skos:description: An identifier for a Media instance.

dcterms:title: EventMedia
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: EventMedia
skos:description: A term to describe the content of the image by a value from a controlled vocabulary.
skos:note: Controlled vocabulary of subjects to support broad classification of media items. Terms from various controlled vocabularies may be used. AC-recommended vocabularies are preferred and MAY be unqualified literals (not a full URI). For terms from other vocabularies either a precise URI SHOULD be used, or, as long as all unqualified terms in all vocabularies are unique, metadata SHOULD provide the source vocabularies using the Subject Category Vocabulary term. The value SHOULD be a string, whose text can also be in the form of a URL. These guidelines on value format are less restrictive than is specified by the IPTC guidelines.

dcterms:title: EventMedia
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the subject category of the Media instance.

dcterms:title: EventMedia
skos:description: Any vocabulary or formal classification from which terms in the Subject Category have been drawn.
skos:note: The AC recommended vocabularies do not need to be cited here. There is no required linkage between individual Subject Category terms and the vocabulary; the mechanism is intended to support discovery of the normative URI for a term, but not guarantee it.

dcterms:title: EventProtocol
skos:description: An identifier for a Protocol.

dcterms:title: EventProtocol
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: An identifier for a broader dwc:Event that groups this and potentially other dwc:Events.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The name of a dwc:Event preferred in searches and results.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in dwc:eventType is given.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A name for a dataset from which data originated.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: An identifier for a dataset from which data originated.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: An identifier given to a dwc:Event in the field.
skos:note: Often serves as a link between field notes and a dwc:Event.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations responsible for conducting or recording a dwc:Event.
skos:example: `José E. Crespo`; `Oliver P. Pearson | Anita K. Pearson`, `FMNH`

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: An identifier for the Agent responsible for conducting or recording a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The date or time interval during which a dwc:Event occurred.
skos:note: For gathering dwc:Events, this is the date-time when the gathering took place.
skos:example: `1963-03-08T14:07-0600` (8 Mar 1963 at 2:07pm in the time zone six hours earlier than UTC); `2009-02-20T08:40Z` (20 February 2009 8:40am UTC); `2018-08-29T15:19` (3:19pm local time on 29 August 2018); `1809-02-12` (some time during 12 February 1809); `1906-06` (some time in June 1906); `1971` (some time in the year 1971); `2007-03-01T13:00:00Z/2008-05-11T15:30:00Z` (some time during the interval between 1 March 2007 1pm UTC and 11 May 2008 3:30pm UTC); `1900/1909` (some time during the interval between the beginning of the year 1900 and the end of the year 1909); `2007-11-13/15` (some time in the interval between 13 November 2007 and 15 November 2007)

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The time or interval during which a dwc:Event occurred.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a time of day that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.
skos:example: `14:07-0600` (2:07pm in the time zone six hours earlier than UTC); `08:40:21Z` (8:40:21am UTC); `13:00:00Z/15:30:00Z` (the interval between 1pm UTC and 3:30pm UTC)

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The earliest integer day of the year on which a dwc:Event occurred (1 for January 1, 365 for December 31, except in a leap year, in which case it is 366).
skos:example: `1` (1 January); `32` (1 February); `366` (31 December); `365` (30 December in a leap year, 31 December in a non-leap year)

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The latest integer day of the year on which a dwc:Event occurred (1 for January 1, 365 for December 31, except in a leap year, in which case it is 366).
skos:example: `1` (1 January); `32` (1 February); `366` (31 December); `365` (30 December in a leap year, 31 December in a non-leap year)

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The four-digit year in which a dwc:Event occurred, according to the Common Era Calendar.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The integer month in which a dwc:Event occurred.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The integer day of the month on which a dwc:Event occurred.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The verbatim original representation of the date and time information for a dwc:Event.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The original textual description of a dcterms:Location of a dwc:Event.
skos:example: `25 km NNE Bariloche por R. Nac. 237`

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The original description of the elevation (altitude, usually above sea level) of a dcterms:Location.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The original description of the depth below a local surface.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The verbatim original spatial coordinates of a dcterms:Location.
skos:note: The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The verbatim original latitude of a dcterms:Location.
skos:note: The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The verbatim original longitude of a dcterms:Location.
skos:note: The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The coordinate format for dwc:verbatimLatitude and dwc:verbatimLongitude or dwc:verbatimCoordinates.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The ellipsoid, geodetic datum, or spatial reference system (SRS) upon which coordinates given in dwc:verbatimLatitude and dwc:verbatimLongitude, or dwc:verbatimCoordinates are based.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use the EPSG code of the SRS, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the geodetic datum, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the ellipsoid, if known. If none of these is known, use the value `unknown`.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A categorical description of the extent to which the georeference has been verified to represent the best possible spatial description for the dcterms:Location of a dwc:Occurrence.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.
skos:example: `unable to georeference`; `requires georeference`; `requires verification`; `verified by data custodian`; `verified by contributor`

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A category or description of the habitat in which a dwc:Event occurred.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A numeric value for a measurement of the size (time duration, length, area, or volume) of a sample in a sampling dwc:Event.
skos:note: A dwc:sampleSizeValue must have a corresponding dwc:sampleSizeUnit.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The unit of measurement of the size (time duration, length, area, or volume) of a sample in a sampling dwc:Event.
skos:note: A dwc:sampleSizeUnit must have a corresponding dwc:sampleSizeValue, e.g., `5` for dwc:sampleSizeValue with `metre` for dwc:sampleSizeUnit.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The amount of effort expended during a dwc:Event.
skos:example: `40 trap-nights`; `10 observer-hours`; `10 km by foot`; `30 km by car`

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: One of a) an indicator of the existence of, b) a reference to (publication, URI), or c) the text of notes taken in the field about a dwc:Event.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/322/5899/261`; `Christopher J. Conroy, Jennifer L. Neuwald. 2008. Phylogeographic study of the California vole, Microtus californicus Journal of Mammalogy, 89(3):755-767.`; `Steven R. Hoofer and Ronald A. Van Den Bussche. 2001. Phylogenetic Relationships of Plecotine Bats and Allies Based on Mitochondrial Ribosomal Sequences. Journal of Mammalogy 82(1):131-137. | Walker, Faith M., Jeffrey T. Foster, Kevin P. Drees, Carol L. Chambers. 2014. Spotted bat (Euderma maculatum) microsatellite discovery using illumina sequencing. Conservation Genetics Resources.`

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dwc:Event.
skos:example: `After the recent rains the river is nearly at flood stage.`

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: An identifier a dcterms:Location.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: An identifier for the geographic region within which the dcterms:Location occurred.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.
skos:example: `http://vocab.getty.edu/tgn/1002002`  (Antártida e Islas del Atlántico Sur, Territorio Nacional de la Tierra del Fuego, Argentina).

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of geographic names less specific than the information captured in dwc:locality.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `), with terms in order from least specific to most specific.
skos:example: `North Atlantic Ocean`; `South America | Argentina | Patagonia | Parque Nacional Nahuel Huapi | Neuquén | Los Lagos` with accompanying values `South America` (continent) `Argentina` (country), `Neuquén` (first order division), and `Los Lagos` (second order division)

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The name of the continent in which the dcterms:Location occurs.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names. Recommended best practice is to leave this field blank if the dcterms:Location spans multiple entities at this administrative level or if the dcterms:Location might be in one or another of multiple possible entities at this level. Multiplicity and uncertainty of the geographic entity can be captured either in the term dwc:higherGeography or in the term dwc:locality, or both.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The name of the water body in which a dcterms:Location occurs.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The name of the island group in which a dcterms:Location occurs.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The name of the island on or near which a dcterms:Location occurs.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The name of the country or major administrative unit in which the dcterms:Location occurs.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names. Recommended best practice is to leave this field blank if the dcterms:Location spans multiple entities at this administrative level or if the dcterms:Location might be in one or another of multiple possible entities at this level. Multiplicity and uncertainty of the geographic entity can be captured either in the term dwc:higherGeography or in the term dwc:locality, or both.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The standard code for the country in which the dcterms:Location occurs.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an ISO 3166-1-alpha-2 country code. Recommended best practice is to leave this field blank if the dcterms:Location spans multiple entities at this administrative level or if the dcterms:Location might be in one or another of multiple possible entities at this level. Multiplicity and uncertainty of the geographic entity can be captured either in the term dwc:higherGeography or in the term dwc:locality, or both.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The name of the next smaller administrative region than country (state, province, canton, department, region, etc.) in which a dcterms:Location occurs.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names. Recommended best practice is to leave this field blank if a dcterms:Location spans multiple entities at this administrative level or if a dcterms:Location might be in one or another of multiple possible entities at this level. Multiplicity and uncertainty of the geographic entity can be captured either in the term dwc:higherGeography or in the term dwc:locality, or both.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region than dwc:stateProvince (county, shire, department, etc.) in which the dcterms:Location occurs.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names. Recommended best practice is to leave this field blank if the dcterms:Location spans multiple entities at this administrative level or if the dcterms:Location might be in one or another of multiple possible entities at this level. Multiplicity and uncertainty of the geographic entity can be captured either in the term dwc:higherGeography or in the term dwc:locality, or both.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region than county (city, municipality, etc.) in which a dcterms:Location occurs. Do not use this term for a nearby named place that does not contain the actual location.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names. Recommended best practice is to leave this field blank if a dcterms:Location spans multiple entities at this administrative level or if a dcterms:Location might be in one or another of multiple possible entities at this level. Multiplicity and uncertainty of the geographic entity can be captured either in the term `higherGeography` or in the term `locality`, or both.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The specific description of the place.
skos:note: Less specific geographic information can be provided in other geographic terms (higherGeography, continent, country, stateProvince, county, municipality, waterBody, island, islandGroup). This term may contain information modified from the original to correct perceived errors or standardize the description.
skos:example: `Bariloche, 25 km NNE via Ruta Nacional 40 (=Ruta 237)`; `Queets Rainforest, Olympic National Park`

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The lower limit of the range of elevation (altitude, usually above sea level), in meters.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The upper limit of the range of elevation (altitude, usually above sea level), in meters.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The vertical datum used as the reference upon which the values in the elevation terms are based.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The lesser depth of a range of depth below the local surface, in meters.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The greater depth of a range of depth below the local surface, in meters.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The lesser distance in a range of distance from a reference surface in the vertical direction, in meters. Use positive values for locations above the surface, negative values for locations below. If depth measures are given, the reference surface is the location given by the depth, otherwise the reference surface is the location given by the elevation.
skos:example: `-1.5` (below the surface); `4.2` (above the surface); For a 1.5 meter sediment core from the bottom of a lake (at depth 20m) at 300m elevation: verbatimElevation: `300m` minimumElevationInMeters: `300`, maximumElevationInMeters: `300`, verbatimDepth: `20m`, minimumDepthInMeters: `20`, maximumDepthInMeters: `20`, minimumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters: `0`, maximumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters: `-1.5`.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The greater distance in a range of distance from a reference surface in the vertical direction, in meters. Use positive values for locations above the surface, negative values for locations below. If depth measures are given, the reference surface is the location given by the depth, otherwise the reference surface is the location given by the elevation.
skos:example: `-1.5` (below the surface); `4.2` (above the surface); For a 1.5 meter sediment core from the bottom of a lake (at depth 20m) at 300m elevation: verbatimElevation: `300m` minimumElevationInMeters: `300`, maximumElevationInMeters: `300`, verbatimDepth: `20m`, minimumDepthInMeters: `20`, maximumDepthInMeters: `20`, minimumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters: `0`, maximumDistanceAboveSurfaceInMeters: `-1.5`.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dcterms:Location.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The geographic latitude (in decimal degrees, using the spatial reference system given in dwc:geodeticDatum) of the geographic center of a dcterms:Location.
skos:note: Positive values are north of the Equator, negative values are south of it. Legal values lie between -90 and 90, inclusive.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The geographic longitude (in decimal degrees, using the spatial reference system given in dwc:geodeticDatum) of the geographic center of a dcterms:Location.
skos:note: Positive values are east of the Greenwich Meridian, negative values are west of it. Legal values lie between -180 and 180, inclusive.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The ellipsoid, geodetic datum, or spatial reference system (SRS) upon which the geographic coordinates given in dwc:decimalLatitude and dwc:decimalLongitude as based.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use the EPSG code of the SRS, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the geodetic datum, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the ellipsoid, if known. If none of these is known, use the value `unknown`.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The horizontal distance (in meters) from the given dwc:decimalLatitude and dwc:decimalLongitude describing the smallest circle containing the whole of the dcterms:Location.
skos:note: Leave the value empty if the uncertainty is unknown, cannot be estimated, or is not applicable (because there are no coordinates). Zero is not a valid value for this term.
skos:example: `30` (reasonable lower limit on or after 2000-05-01 of a GPS reading under good conditions if the actual precision was not recorded at the time); `100` (reasonable lower limit before 2000-05-01 of a GPS reading under good conditions if the actual precision was not recorded at the time); `71` (uncertainty for a UTM coordinate having 100 meter precision and a known spatial reference system)

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A decimal representation of the precision of the coordinates given in a dwc:decimalLatitude and dwc:decimalLongitude.
skos:example: `0.00001` (normal GPS limit for decimal degrees); `0.000278` (nearest second); `0.01667` (nearest minute); `1.0` (nearest degree)

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The ratio of the area of the point-radius (dwc:decimalLatitude, dwc:decimalLongitude, dwc:coordinateUncertaintyInMeters) to the area of the true (original, or most specific) spatial representation of a dcterms:Location.
skos:note: Legal values are 0, greater than or equal to 1, or undefined. A value of 1 is an exact match or 100% overlap. A value of 0 should be used if the given point-radius does not completely contain the original representation. The pointRadiusSpatialFit is undefined (and should be left empty) if the original representation is any geometry without area (e.g., a point or polyline) and without uncertainty and the given georeference is not that same geometry (without uncertainty). If both the original and the given georeference are the same point, the pointRadiusSpatialFit is 1. Detailed explanations with graphical examples can be found in the Georeferencing Best Practices, Chapman and Wieczorek, 2020 (https://doi.org/10.15468/doc-gg7h-s853).

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A Well-Known Text (WKT) representation of the shape (footprint, geometry) that defines a dcterms:Location.
skos:note: A dcterms:Location may have both a point-radius representation (see dwc:decimalLatitude) and a footprint representation, and they may differ from each other.
skos:example: `POLYGON ((10 20, 11 20, 11 21, 10 21, 10 20))` (the one-degree bounding box with opposite corners at longitude=10, latitude=20 and longitude=11, latitude=21)

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The ellipsoid, geodetic datum, or spatial reference system (SRS) upon which the geometry given in dwc:footprintWKT is based.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use the EPSG code of the SRS, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the geodetic datum, if known. Otherwise use a controlled vocabulary for the name or code of the ellipsoid, if known. If none of these is known, use the value `unknown`. It is also permitted to provide the SRS in Well-Known-Text, especially if no EPSG code provides the necessary values for the attributes of the SRS. Do not use this term to describe the SRS of a dwc:decimalLatitude and dwc:decimalLongitude, nor of any verbatim coordinates - use dwc:geodeticDatum and dwc:verbatimSRS instead.
skos:example: `epsg:4326`; `GEOGCS['GCS_WGS_1984', DATUM['D_WGS_1984', SPHEROID['WGS_1984',6378137,298.257223563]], PRIMEM['Greenwich',0], UNIT['Degree',0.0174532925199433]]` (WKT for the standard WGS84 Spatial Reference System EPSG:4326)

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The ratio of the area of the footprint (footprintWKT) to the area of the true (original, or most specific) spatial representation of a dcterms:Location.
skos:note: Legal values are 0, greater than or equal to 1, or undefined. A value of 1 is an exact match or 100% overlap. A value of 0 should be used if the given footprint does not completely contain the original representation. The dwc:footprintSpatialFit is undefined (and should be left empty) if the original representation is any geometry without area (e.g., a point or polyline) and without uncertainty and the given georeference is not that same geometry (without uncertainty). If both the original and the given georeference are the same point, a dwc:footprintSpatialFit is 1.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who determined a georeference (spatial representation) for a dcterms:Location.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: An identifier for the Agent who georeferenced a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: The date on which a dcterms:Location was georeferenced.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A description or reference to the methods used to determine the spatial footprint, coordinates, and uncertainties.
skos:example: `Georeferencing Quick Reference Guide (Zermoglio et al. 2020, https://doi.org/10.35035/e09p-h128)`

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: An identifier for a Protocol used to georeference a dwc:Event.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of maps, gazetteers, or other resources used to georeference a dcterms:Location, described specifically enough to allow anyone in the future to use the same resources.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `https://www.geonames.org/`; `USGS 1:24000 Florence Montana Quad 1967 | Terrametrics 2008 on Google Earth`; `GeoLocate`

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: Comments or notes about a spatial description determination, explaining assumptions made in addition or opposition to the those formalized in the method referred to in dwc:georeferenceProtocol.

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: Additional information that exists, but that has not been shared in the given record.
skos:example: `location information not given for endangered species`; `collector identities withheld | ask about tissue samples`

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: Actions taken to make the shared data less specific or complete than in its original form. Suggests that alternative data of higher quality may be available on request.
skos:example: `coordinates generalized from original GPS coordinates to the nearest half degree grid cell`

dcterms:title: Event
skos:description: An indication of which spatial representation best represents the dcterms:Location.

dcterms:title: GeneticSequenceAgentRole

skos:note: One could use agentRoleOrder to create an ordered list of collectors (agentRole = 'collector') for a dwc:MaterialEntity, for example. The first would have agentRoleOrder=1, the second would have agentRoleOrder=2.

skos:example: `mass`; `mean mass`; `weight standard deviation`; `minimum organism quantity`; `water temperature`; `salinity`

skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: GeneticSequenceAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionType is given.

skos:description: The date on which an Assertion was created.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: GeneticSequenceAssertion
skos:description: The date on which the state or measurement of an Assertion was deemed to first be in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: GeneticSequenceAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is not numeric.

dcterms:title: GeneticSequenceAssertion
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the value of an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionValue is given.

dcterms:title: GeneticSequenceAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is numeric.

dcterms:title: GeneticSequenceAssertion
skos:description: The units associated with the value in assertionValueNumeric.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Ontology of Units of Measure http://www.wurvoc.org/vocabularies/om-1.8/ of SI units, derived units, or other non-SI units accepted for use within the SI. For units that are composed of multiple parts, use the patterns as given in "A Primer for Communicating Mathematics via Plain Text" (https://cse.sc.edu/~fenner/latex-ASCII.pdf) by Stephen Fenner (e.g., `g/cm^3` for grams per cubic centimeter). For other units, provide the value as a recognizable standard (e.g., '%') or written out in full and in the plural (e.g., `individuals`). It is fine to provide non-SI units in the original language of the dataset.

dcterms:title: GeneticSequenceAssertion
skos:description: The IRI for the units of an assertionValueNumeric.

dcterms:title: GeneticSequenceAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionUnit is given.

dcterms:title: GeneticSequenceAssertion

skos:example: `José E. Crespo`; `Oliver P. Pearson | Anita K. Pearson`, `FMNH`

dcterms:title: GeneticSequenceAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent who made an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.
skos:example: `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097` (for an individual); `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097 | https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0098` (for a list of people)

skos:example: `http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/322/5899/261`; `Christopher J. Conroy, Jennifer L. Neuwald. 2008. Phylogeographic study of the California vole, Microtus californicus Journal of Mammalogy, 89(3):755-767.`; `Steven R. Hoofer and Ronald A. Van Den Bussche. 2001. Phylogenetic Relationships of Plecotine Bats and Allies Based on Mitochondrial Ribosomal Sequences. Journal of Mammalogy 82(1):131-137. | Walker, Faith M., Jeffrey T. Foster, Kevin P. Drees, Carol L. Chambers. 2014. Spotted bat (Euderma maculatum) microsatellite discovery using illumina sequencing. Conservation Genetics Resources.`

The intended usage of this term in Darwin Core is to provide the preferred way to cite the resource itself. Note that the intended usage of dcterms:references in Darwin Core, by contrast, is to point to the definitive source representation of the resource, if one is available.
skos:example: `Museum of Vertebrate Zoology, UC Berkeley. MVZ Mammal Collection (Arctos). Record ID: http://arctos.database.museum/guid/MVZ:Mamm:165861?seid=101356. Source: http://ipt.vertnet.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=mvz_mammal.` (Occurrence example); `https://www.gbif.org/species/2439608 Source: GBIF Taxonomic Backbone` (Taxon example); `Rand, K.M., Logerwell, E.A. Note that the intended usage of dcterms:references in Darwin Core, by contrast, is to point to the definitive source representation of the resource, if one is available.

AC-recommended vocabularies are preferred and MAY be unqualified literals (not a full URI). For terms from other vocabularies either a precise URI SHOULD be used, or, as long as all unqualified terms in all vocabularies are unique, metadata SHOULD provide the source vocabularies using the Subject Category Vocabulary term. The value SHOULD be a string, whose text can also be in the form of a URL. These guidelines on value format are less restrictive than is specified by the IPTC guidelines.

skos:description: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic eon or lowest chrono-stratigraphic eonothem or the informal name ('Precambrian') attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic eon or highest chrono-stratigraphic eonothem or the informal name ('Precambrian') attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic era or lowest chronostratigraphic erathem attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic era or highest chronostratigraphic erathem attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic period or lowest chronostratigraphic system attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic period or highest chronostratigraphic system attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic epoch or lowest chronostratigraphic series attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic epoch or highest chronostratigraphic series attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic age or lowest chronostratigraphic stage attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the latest possible geochronologic age or highest chronostratigraphic stage attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the lowest possible geological biostratigraphic zone of the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the highest possible geological biostratigraphic zone of the stratigraphic horizon from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The combination of all litho-stratigraphic names for the rock from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the lithostratigraphic group from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the lithostratigraphic formation from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the lithostratigraphic member from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: GeologicalContext
skos:description: The full name of the lithostratigraphic bed from which a dwc:MaterialEntity was collected.

dcterms:title: IdentificationAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: IdentificationAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Identification.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: IdentificationAgentRole
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary for the roles appropriate to the class of resource an AgentRole is related to.

dcterms:title: IdentificationAgentRole
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: IdentificationAgentRole
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for agentRole is given.

dcterms:title: IdentificationAgentRole
skos:description: The numerical position of an AgentRole in a set of AgentRoles that have the same combination of agentRole, agentRoleIRI, agentRoleVocabulary and related target.
skos:note: One could use agentRoleOrder to create an ordered list of collectors (agentRole = 'collector') for a dwc:MaterialEntity, for example. The first would have agentRoleOrder=1, the second would have agentRoleOrder=2.

dcterms:title: IdentificationAgentRole
skos:description: The interval during which an AgentRole was in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: IdentificationTaxon
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Identification.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: IdentificationTaxon
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Taxon.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: IdentificationTaxon
skos:description: The position of a dwc:Taxon in a taxonFormula.

dcterms:title: IdentificationTaxon
skos:description: The full scientific name of the kingdom in which a dwc:scientificName is classified.

dcterms:title: IdentificationTaxon
skos:description: The full scientific name, with authorship and date information if known. When forming part of a dwc:Identification, this should be the name in lowest level taxonomic rank that can be determined. This term should not contain identification qualifications, which should instead be supplied in dwc:verbatimIdentification.

dcterms:title: IdentificationTaxon
skos:description: The taxonomic rank of the most specific name in a dwc:scientificName.

dcterms:title: IdentificationTaxon
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dwc:Taxon.
skos:example: `this name is a misspelling in common use`

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Identification.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Occurrence based on which a dwc:Identification was made.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:MaterialEntity based on which a dwc:Identification was made.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: An identifier for a GeneticSequence based on which a dwc:Identification was made.

dcterms:title: Identification
