skos:description: An identifier for a Media instance based on which a dwc:Identification was made.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a dwc:Identification.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of dwc:Identification.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary..

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in identificationType is given.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: A string representing the taxonomic identification as it appeared in the original record.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: The dwc:Identification of a dwc:Organism is a currently accepted one.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: A string representing the pattern to use to construct a dwc:Identification from dwc:Taxon names and identification qualifiers.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as https://arctos.database.museum/info/ctDocumentation.cfm?table=cttaxa_formula.
skos:example: `A`; `A ?`; `A or B`; `A and B`; `A x B`; `A cf.`; `A aff.`

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of nomenclatural types (type status, typified scientific name, publication) applied to the subject.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space ( | ). This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.
skos:example: `holotype of Ctenomys sociabilis. Pearson O. P., and M. I. Christie. 1985. Historia Natural, 5(37):388`; `holotype of Pinus abies | holotype of Picea abies`

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a type designation.
skos:note: From https://rs.gbif.org/extension/gbif/1.0/typesandspecimen.xml.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who made a taxonomic determination of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: The identifier for the Agent who made a taxonomic determination of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to provide a single identifier that disambiguates the details of the identifying agent. If a list is used, the order of the identifiers on the list should not be assumed to convey any semantics. Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who made a taxonomic determination of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of references (publication, global unique identifier, URI) used in a dwc:Identification.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `Aves del Noroeste Patagonico. Christie et al. 2004.`; `Stebbins, R. Field Guide to Western Reptiles and Amphibians. 3rd Edition. 2003. | Irschick, D.J. and Shaffer, H.B. (1997). The polytypic species revisited: Morphological differentiation among tiger salamanders (Ambystoma tigrinum) (Amphibia: Caudata). Herpetologica, 53(1), 30-49.`

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: A categorical indicator of the extent to which the taxonomic identification has been verified to be correct.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as that used in HISPID and ABCD.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for an identification verification.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for dwc:identificationVerificationStatus is given.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dwc:Identification.
skos:example: `Distinguished between Anthus correndera and Anthus hellmayri based on the comparative lengths of the uñas.`

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Taxon.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: The full scientific name of the kingdom in which a dwc:scientificName is classified.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: The full scientific name, with authorship and date information if known. When forming part of a dwc:Identification, this should be the name in lowest level taxonomic rank that can be determined. This term should not contain identification qualifications, which should instead be supplied in dwc:verbatimIdentification.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: The taxonomic rank of the most specific name in a dwc:scientificName.

dcterms:title: Identification
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dwc:Taxon.
skos:example: `this name is a misspelling in common use`

dcterms:title: MaterialAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: MaterialAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Values of dwc:materialEntityID are intended to uniquely and persistently identify a particular dwc:MaterialEntity within some context. Examples of context include a particular sample collection, an organization, or the worldwide scale. Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. The identifier is bound to a physical object (a dwc:MaterialEntity) as opposed to a particular digital record (representation) of that physical object.

dcterms:title: MaterialAgentRole
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary for the roles appropriate to the class of resource an AgentRole is related to.

dcterms:title: MaterialAgentRole
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: MaterialAgentRole
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for agentRole is given.

dcterms:title: MaterialAgentRole
skos:description: The numerical position of an AgentRole in a set of AgentRoles that have the same combination of agentRole, agentRoleIRI, agentRoleVocabulary and related target.
skos:note: One could use agentRoleOrder to create an ordered list of collectors (agentRole = 'collector') for a dwc:MaterialEntity, for example. The first would have agentRoleOrder=1, the second would have agentRoleOrder=2.

dcterms:title: MaterialAgentRole
skos:description: The interval during which an AgentRole was in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Values of dwc:materialEntityID are intended to uniquely and persistently identify a particular dwc:MaterialEntity within some context. Examples of context include a particular sample collection, an organization, or the worldwide scale. Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. The identifier is bound to a physical object (a dwc:MaterialEntity) as opposed to a particular digital record (representation) of that physical object.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of an Assertion.
skos:example: `mass`; `mean mass`; `weight standard deviation`; `minimum organism quantity`; `water temperature`; `salinity`

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionType is given.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: The date on which an Assertion was created.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: The date on which the state or measurement of an Assertion was deemed to first be in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is not numeric.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the value of an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionValue is given.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is numeric.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: The units associated with the value in assertionValueNumeric.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Ontology of Units of Measure http://www.wurvoc.org/vocabularies/om-1.8/ of SI units, derived units, or other non-SI units accepted for use within the SI. For units that are composed of multiple parts, use the patterns as given in "A Primer for Communicating Mathematics via Plain Text" (https://cse.sc.edu/~fenner/latex-ASCII.pdf) by Stephen Fenner (e.g., `g/cm^3` for grams per cubic centimeter). For other units, provide the value as a recognizable standard (e.g., '%') or written out in full and in the plural (e.g., `individuals`). It is fine to provide non-SI units in the original language of the dataset.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: The IRI for the units of an assertionValueNumeric.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionUnit is given.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who made an Assertion.
skos:example: `José E. Crespo`; `Oliver P. Pearson | Anita K. Pearson`, `FMNH`

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent who made an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.
skos:example: `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097` (for an individual); `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097 | https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0098` (for a list of people)

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: The names of, references to, or descriptions of the methods or protocols used in making an Assertion.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for a Protocol used to make an Assertion.

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/322/5899/261`; `Christopher J. Conroy, Jennifer L. Neuwald. 2008. Phylogeographic study of the California vole, Microtus californicus Journal of Mammalogy, 89(3):755-767.`; `Steven R. Hoofer and Ronald A. Van Den Bussche. 2001. Phylogenetic Relationships of Plecotine Bats and Allies Based on Mitochondrial Ribosomal Sequences. Journal of Mammalogy 82(1):131-137. | Walker, Faith M., Jeffrey T. Foster, Kevin P. Drees, Carol L. Chambers. 2014. Spotted bat (Euderma maculatum) microsatellite discovery using illumina sequencing. Conservation Genetics Resources.`

dcterms:title: MaterialAssertion
skos:description: Comments or notes about an Assertion.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: An identifier for a Citation.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Values of dwc:materialEntityID are intended to uniquely and persistently identify a particular dwc:MaterialEntity within some context. Examples of context include a particular sample collection, an organization, or the worldwide scale. Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. The identifier is bound to a physical object (a dwc:MaterialEntity) as opposed to a particular digital record (representation) of that physical object.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a Citation.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Citation.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in citationType is given.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: A bibliographic reference for the resource.
skos:note: From Dublin Core, 'Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.' The intended usage of this term in Darwin Core is to provide the preferred way to cite the resource itself. Note that the intended usage of dcterms:references in Darwin Core, by contrast, is to point to the definitive source representation of the resource, if one is available.
skos:example: `Museum of Vertebrate Zoology, UC Berkeley. MVZ Mammal Collection (Arctos). Record ID: http://arctos.database.museum/guid/MVZ:Mamm:165861?seid=101356. Source: http://ipt.vertnet.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=mvz_mammal.` (Occurrence example); `https://www.gbif.org/species/2439608 Source: GBIF Taxonomic Backbone` (Taxon example); `Rand, K.M., Logerwell, E.A. The first demersal trawl survey of benthic fish and invertebrates in the Beaufort Sea since the late 1970s. Polar Biol 34, 475–488 (2011). https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-010-0900-2` (Event example)

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: The number of the page on which the citation occurs in the cited reference.
skos:note: From Dublin Core, 'Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.' The intended usage of this term in Darwin Core is to provide the preferred way to cite the resource itself. Note that the intended usage of dcterms:references in Darwin Core, by contrast, is to point to the definitive source representation of the resource, if one is available.
skos:example: `Museum of Vertebrate Zoology, UC Berkeley. MVZ Mammal Collection (Arctos). Record ID: http://arctos.database.museum/guid/MVZ:Mamm:165861?seid=101356. Source: http://ipt.vertnet.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=mvz_mammal.` (Occurrence example); `https://www.gbif.org/species/2439608 Source: GBIF Taxonomic Backbone` (Taxon example); `Rand, K.M., Logerwell, E.A. The first demersal trawl survey of benthic fish and invertebrates in the Beaufort Sea since the late 1970s. Polar Biol 34, 475–488 (2011). https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-010-0900-2` (Event example)

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: An identifier for the reference in which a Citation occurs.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a reference.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of reference.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in referenceType is given.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: The year the reference in a Citation was published.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: An indication of whether the reference for a Citation was peer reviewed.

dcterms:title: MaterialCitation
skos:description: Comments or notes about a Citation.

dcterms:title: MaterialIdentifier
skos:description: An unambiguous reference to a resource within a given context.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to identify a resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.

dcterms:title: MaterialIdentifier
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Values of dwc:materialEntityID are intended to uniquely and persistently identify a particular dwc:MaterialEntity within some context. Examples of context include a particular sample collection, an organization, or the worldwide scale. Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. The identifier is bound to a physical object (a dwc:MaterialEntity) as opposed to a particular digital record (representation) of that physical object.

dcterms:title: MaterialIdentifier
skos:description: The category or system that best matches the nature of an Identifier.

dcterms:title: MaterialIdentifier
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Identifier.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: MaterialIdentifier
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in identifierType is given.

dcterms:title: MaterialIdentifier
skos:description: A language in which an Identifier is presented.
skos:note: Recommended best prectice is to use an ISO639-2 three-letter language code.

dcterms:title: MaterialMedia
skos:description: An identifier for a Media instance.

dcterms:title: MaterialMedia
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Values of dwc:materialEntityID are intended to uniquely and persistently identify a particular dwc:MaterialEntity within some context. Examples of context include a particular sample collection, an organization, or the worldwide scale. Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. The identifier is bound to a physical object (a dwc:MaterialEntity) as opposed to a particular digital record (representation) of that physical object.

dcterms:title: MaterialMedia
skos:description: A term to describe the content of the image by a value from a controlled vocabulary.
skos:note: Controlled vocabulary of subjects to support broad classification of media items. Terms from various controlled vocabularies may be used. AC-recommended vocabularies are preferred and MAY be unqualified literals (not a full URI). For terms from other vocabularies either a precise URI SHOULD be used, or, as long as all unqualified terms in all vocabularies are unique, metadata SHOULD provide the source vocabularies using the Subject Category Vocabulary term. The value SHOULD be a string, whose text can also be in the form of a URL. These guidelines on value format are less restrictive than is specified by the IPTC guidelines.

dcterms:title: MaterialMedia
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the subject category of the Media instance.

dcterms:title: MaterialMedia
skos:description: Any vocabulary or formal classification from which terms in the Subject Category have been drawn.
skos:note: The AC recommended vocabularies do not need to be cited here. There is no required linkage between individual Subject Category terms and the vocabulary; the mechanism is intended to support discovery of the normative URI for a term, but not guarantee it.

dcterms:title: MaterialProtocol
skos:description: An identifier for a Protocol.

dcterms:title: MaterialProtocol
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Values of dwc:materialEntityID are intended to uniquely and persistently identify a particular dwc:MaterialEntity within some context. Examples of context include a particular sample collection, an organization, or the worldwide scale. Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. The identifier is bound to a physical object (a dwc:MaterialEntity) as opposed to a particular digital record (representation) of that physical object.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Values of dwc:materialEntityID are intended to uniquely and persistently identify a particular dwc:MaterialEntity within some context. Examples of context include a particular sample collection, an organization, or the worldwide scale. Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. The identifier is bound to a physical object (a dwc:MaterialEntity) as opposed to a particular digital record (representation) of that physical object.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The broad category that best matches the nature of a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a limited, tightly controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The narrow category that best matches the nature of a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.
skos:example: `whole organism`; `heart`; `liver tissue sample`; `fossil`; `germplasm`; `skull`; `cast`; `3D printed model`; `printed photograph`

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in materialEntityType is given.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The name (or acronym) in use by an institution.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier for an institution.
skos:note: For physical specimens, the recommended best practice is to use a globally unique and resolvable identifier from a collections registry such as the Research Organization Registry (ROR) or the GBIF Registry of Scientific Collections (https://www.gbif.org/grscicoll).

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having ownership of a dwc:MaterialEntity.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier for an institution that owns a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: For physical specimens, the recommended best practice is to use a globally unique and resolvable identifier from a collections registry such as the Research Organization Registry (ROR) or the GBIF Registry of Scientific Collections (https://www.gbif.org/grscicoll).

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The name, acronym, coden, or initialism identifying a Collection.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier for a Collection.
skos:note: For physical specimens, the recommended best practice is to use a globally unique and resolvable identifier from a collections registry such as the GBIF Registry of Scientific Collections (https://www.gbif.org/grscicoll).

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier (preferably unique) for a dwc:MaterialEntity within a Collection.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of previous or alternate fully qualified catalog numbers or other human-used identifiers for the same dwc:MaterialEntity, whether in the current or any other data set or collection.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations responsible for collecting a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:example: `José E. Crespo`; `Oliver P. Pearson | Anita K. Pearson`, `FMNH`

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier for the Agent responsible for collecting a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The number of distinct objects comprising a dwc:MaterialEntity.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier given to a dwc:MaterialEntity at the time it was recorded. Often serves as a link between field notes and a dwc:MaterialEntity, such as a specimen collector's number.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of preparations and preservation methods for a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The current state of a dwc:MaterialEntity with respect to where it can be found.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The content of this term should include no embellishments, prefixes, headers or other additions made to the text. Abbreviations must not be expanded and supposed misspellings must not be corrected. Lines or breakpoints between blocks of text that could be verified by seeing the original labels or images of them may be used. Examples of material entities include preserved specimens, fossil specimens, and material samples. Best practice is to use UTF-8 for all characters. Best practice is to add comment “verbatimLabel derived from human transcription” in dwc:occurrenceRemarks.
skos:note: Examples can be found at https://dwc.tdwg.org/examples/verbatimLabel.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, global unique identifier, URI) of genetic sequence information associated with a dwc:MaterialEntity.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `Christopher J. Conroy, Jennifer L. Neuwald. 2008. Phylogeographic study of the California vole, Microtus californicus Journal of Mammalogy, 89(3):755-767.`; `Steven R. Hoofer and Ronald A. Van Den Bussche. 2001. Phylogenetic Relationships of Plecotine Bats and Allies Based on Mitochondrial Ribosomal Sequences. Journal of Mammalogy 82(1):131-137. | Walker, Faith M., Jeffrey T. Foster, Kevin P. Drees, Carol L. Chambers. 2014. Spotted bat (Euderma maculatum) microsatellite discovery using illumina sequencing. Conservation Genetics Resources.`

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: Additional information that exists, but that has not been shared in the given record.
skos:example: `location information not given for endangered species`; `collector identities withheld | ask about tissue samples`

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: Actions taken to make the shared data less specific or complete than in its original form. Suggests that alternative data of higher quality may be available on request.
skos:example: `coordinates generalized from original GPS coordinates to the nearest half degree grid cell`

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:example: `found in association with charred remains`; `some original fragments missing`

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Occurrence for which a dwc:MaterialEntity provides evidence.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:MaterialEntity from which this dwc:MaterialEntity was derived.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Event during which a dwc:MaterialEntity was derived from another dwc:MaterialEntity.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of the derivation of a dwc:MaterialEntity from a dwc:MaterialEntity pointed to by derivedFromMaterialEntityID.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of derivation.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in derivationType is given.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:MaterialEntity of which this dwc:MaterialEntity is a part.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: A string representing the taxonomic identification as it appeared in the original record.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: A string representing the pattern to use to construct a dwc:Identification from dwc:Taxon names and identification qualifiers.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as https://arctos.database.museum/info/ctDocumentation.cfm?table=cttaxa_formula.
skos:example: `A`; `A ?`; `A or B`; `A and B`; `A x B`; `A cf.`; `A aff.`

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who made a taxonomic determination of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The identifier for the Agent who made a taxonomic determination of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to provide a single identifier that disambiguates the details of the identifying agent. If a list is used, the order of the identifiers on the list should not be assumed to convey any semantics. Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who made a taxonomic determination of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of references (publication, global unique identifier, URI) used in a dwc:Identification.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `Aves del Noroeste Patagonico. Christie et al. 2004.`; `Stebbins, R. Field Guide to Western Reptiles and Amphibians. 3rd Edition. 2003. | Irschick, D.J. and Shaffer, H.B. (1997). The polytypic species revisited: Morphological differentiation among tiger salamanders (Ambystoma tigrinum) (Amphibia: Caudata). Herpetologica, 53(1), 30-49.`

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: A categorical indicator of the extent to which the taxonomic determination has been verified to be correct.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as that used in HISPID and ABCD.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for an identification verification.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for dwc:identificationVerificationStatus is given.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dwc:Identification.
skos:example: `Distinguished between Anthus correndera and Anthus hellmayri based on the comparative lengths of the uñas.`

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Taxon.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The full scientific name of the kingdom in which a dwc:scientificName is classified.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The full scientific name, with authorship and date information if known. When forming part of a dwc:Identification, this should be the name in lowest level taxonomic rank that can be determined. This term should not contain identification qualifications, which should instead be supplied in dwc:verbatimIdentification.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: The taxonomic rank of the most specific name in a dwc:scientificName.

dcterms:title: Material
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dwc:Taxon.
skos:example: `this name is a misspelling in common use`

dcterms:title: MediaAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: MediaAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for a Media instance.

dcterms:title: MediaAgentRole
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary for the roles appropriate to the class of resource an AgentRole is related to.

dcterms:title: MediaAgentRole
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: MediaAgentRole
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for agentRole is given.

dcterms:title: MediaAgentRole
skos:description: The numerical position of an AgentRole in a set of AgentRoles that have the same combination of agentRole, agentRoleIRI, agentRoleVocabulary and related target.
skos:note: One could use agentRoleOrder to create an ordered list of collectors (agentRole = 'collector') for a dwc:MaterialEntity, for example. The first would have agentRoleOrder=1, the second would have agentRoleOrder=2.

dcterms:title: MediaAgentRole
skos:description: The interval during which an AgentRole was in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for a Media instance.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of an Assertion.
skos:example: `mass`; `mean mass`; `weight standard deviation`; `minimum organism quantity`; `water temperature`; `salinity`

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionType is given.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: The date on which an Assertion was created.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: The date on which the state or measurement of an Assertion was deemed to first be in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is not numeric.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the value of an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionValue is given.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is numeric.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: The units associated with the value in assertionValueNumeric.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Ontology of Units of Measure http://www.wurvoc.org/vocabularies/om-1.8/ of SI units, derived units, or other non-SI units accepted for use within the SI. For units that are composed of multiple parts, use the patterns as given in "A Primer for Communicating Mathematics via Plain Text" (https://cse.sc.edu/~fenner/latex-ASCII.pdf) by Stephen Fenner (e.g., `g/cm^3` for grams per cubic centimeter). For other units, provide the value as a recognizable standard (e.g., '%') or written out in full and in the plural (e.g., `individuals`). It is fine to provide non-SI units in the original language of the dataset.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: The IRI for the units of an assertionValueNumeric.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionUnit is given.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who made an Assertion.
skos:example: `José E. Crespo`; `Oliver P. Pearson | Anita K. Pearson`, `FMNH`

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent who made an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.
skos:example: `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097` (for an individual); `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097 | https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0098` (for a list of people)

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: The names of, references to, or descriptions of the methods or protocols used in making an Assertion.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for a Protocol used to make an Assertion.

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/322/5899/261`; `Christopher J. Conroy, Jennifer L. Neuwald. 2008. Phylogeographic study of the California vole, Microtus californicus Journal of Mammalogy, 89(3):755-767.`; `Steven R. Hoofer and Ronald A. Van Den Bussche. 2001. Phylogenetic Relationships of Plecotine Bats and Allies Based on Mitochondrial Ribosomal Sequences. Journal of Mammalogy 82(1):131-137. | Walker, Faith M., Jeffrey T. Foster, Kevin P. Drees, Carol L. Chambers. 2014. Spotted bat (Euderma maculatum) microsatellite discovery using illumina sequencing. Conservation Genetics Resources.`

dcterms:title: MediaAssertion
skos:description: Comments or notes about an Assertion.

dcterms:title: MediaIdentifier
skos:description: An unambiguous reference to a resource within a given context.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to identify a resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.

dcterms:title: MediaIdentifier
skos:description: An identifier for a Media instance.

dcterms:title: MediaIdentifier
skos:description: The category or system that best matches the nature of an Identifier.

dcterms:title: MediaIdentifier
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Identifier.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: MediaIdentifier
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in identifierType is given.

dcterms:title: MediaIdentifier
skos:description: A language in which an Identifier is presented.
skos:note: Recommended best prectice is to use an ISO639-2 three-letter language code.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: An identifier for a Media instance.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of an instance of Media.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Media.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in mediaType is given.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: A URI that uniquely identifies a service that provides a representation of the underlying resource.
skos:note: If this resource can be acquired by an http request, its http URL SHOULD be given. If not, but it has some URI in another URI scheme, that MAY be given here. Value might point to something offline, such as a published CD, etc. For example, the doi of a published CD would be a suitable value.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: A Web URL for a statement of the ownership and usage rights for this resource.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: The file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource.
skos:note: A controlled value string describing the technical format of the resource (file format or physical medium). The string SHOULD be a controlled value from the Audiovisual Core Controlled Vocabulary for Dublin Core format, although it MAY be any Media Type (MIME type) value from the IANA list of Media Types (https://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml) or any commonly used file extension string. Human-readable information about the Controlled Vocabulary for format is at http://rs.tdwg.org/ac/doc/format/ . This term can be used to describe offline digital content. In cases where the provided Service Access Point URL includes a standard file extension from which the format can be inferred, it is permissible to not provide a value for this property. See also the entry for dcterms:format in the Audiovisual Core term list document and see the DCMI FAQ on DC and DCTERMS Namespaces, https://web.archive.org/web/20171126043657/https://github.com/dcmi/repository/blob/master/mediawiki_wiki/FAQ/DC_and_DCTERMS_Namespaces.md, for discussion of the rationale for terms in two namespaces. It is best practice to use dcterms:format instead of dc:format whenever practical. Normal practice is to use the same Label if both are provided. Labels have no effect on information discovery and are only suggestions.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: Information about rights held in and over the resource.
skos:note: A full-text, readable copyright statement, as required by the national legislation of the copyright holder. On collections, this applies to all contained objects, unless the object itself has a different statement. Do not place just the name of the copyright holder(s) here! That belongs in a list in the xmpRights:Owner field, which SHOULD be supplied if dc:rights is not 'Public Domain', which is appropriate only if the resource is known to be not under copyright. At least one of dcterms:rights and dc:rights MUST be supplied but, when feasible, supplying both might make the metadata more widely useful. They MUST specify the same rights. This expresses rights over the media resource, not over the metadata text. In case of ambiguity, dcterms:rights prevails. See also the entry for dcterms:rights in the Audiovisual Core Term List document and see the DCMI FAQ on DC and DCTERMS Namespaces, https://web.archive.org/web/20171126043657/https://github.com/dcmi/repository/blob/master/mediawiki_wiki/FAQ/DC_and_DCTERMS_Namespaces.md, for discussion of the rationale for terms in two namespaces. Normal practice is to use the same Label if both are provided. Labels have no effect on information discovery and are only suggestions.
skos:example: `Copyright XY 2008, all rights reserved`; `© 2008 XY Museum`; `Public Domain`; `Copyright unknown`

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: A list of legal owners of the resource.
skos:note: A list of the names of the owners of the copyright. 'Unknown' is an acceptable value, but 'Public Domain' is not. In that case, omit or leave empty xmpRights:Owner, and put 'Public Domain' in the Copyright Statement (dc:rights). Note: Audiovisual Core guidelines on value format are less restrictive than is specified in the IPTC guidelines. Some providers use dc:publisher for this purpose, but it seems doubtful that the publisher is by necessity the copyright owner. 'Public Domain' is not an appropriate value because it denotes something that is not under copyright. Except for 'Public Domain' resources, it is strongly urged that this field be supplied.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.
skos:note: A string providing an identifiable source from which the described resources was derived. If the resource was digitized from a non-digital resource, or was also previously published in a digital or printed publication, this describes the original. Do not put generally "related" publications in here. This field normally contains a free-form text description. If a URI is available it should be provided in dcterms:source. Can be repeatable if a montage of images. Information about further provenance beyond the ultimate source should be put in the derivedFrom attribute. See also the entry for dcterms:source in the Audiovisual Core term list document and see the DCMI FAQ on DC and DCTERMS Namespaces, https://web.archive.org/web/20171126043657/https://github.com/dcmi/repository/blob/master/mediawiki_wiki/FAQ/DC_and_DCTERMS_Namespaces.md, for discussion of the rationale for terms in two namespaces. Normal practice is to use the same Label if both are provided. Labels have no effect on information discovery and are only suggestions.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: An entity primarily responsible for making the resource.
skos:note: The person or organization responsible for creating the media resource. The value MAY be simple text including contact information. Note that the Creator need not be the Copyright Owner. See also the entry for dcterms:creator in the Audiovisual Core term list document and see the DCMI FAQ on DC and DCTERMS Namespaces, https://web.archive.org/web/20171126043657/https://github.com/dcmi/repository/blob/master/mediawiki_wiki/FAQ/DC_and_DCTERMS_Namespaces.md, for discussion of the rationale for terms in two namespaces. Normal practice is to use the same Label if both are provided. Labels have no effect on information discovery and are only suggestions.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: An identifier for the entity primarily responsible for making the resource.
skos:note: An identifier for the person or organization responsible for creating the media resource. Note that the Creator need not be the Copyright Owner. See the entry for dcterms:creator in the Audiovisual Core term list document and see the DCMI FAQ on DC and DCTERMS Namespaces, https://web.archive.org/web/20171126043657/https://github.com/dcmi/repository/blob/master/mediawiki_wiki/FAQ/DC_and_DCTERMS_Namespaces.md, for discussion of the rationale for terms in two namespaces.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: The date and time the resource was created. For a digital file, this need not match a file-system creation time. For a freshly created resource, it should be close to that time, modulo the time taken to write the file. Later file transfer, copying, and so on, can make the file-system time arbitrarily different.
skos:note: The date of the creation of the original resource from which the digital media was derived or created. The date and time MUST comply with the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) datetime practice, https://www.w3.org/TR/NOTE-datetime, which requires that date and time representation correspond to ISO 8601:1998, but with year fields always comprising 4 digits. This makes datetime records compliant with 8601:2004, https://www.iso.org/standard/40874.html. AC datetime values MAY also follow 8601:2004 for ranges by separating two IS0 8601 datetime fields by a solidus ("forward slash", '/'). When applied to a media resource with temporal extent such as audio or video, this property indicates the startTime of the recording. What constitutes "original" is determined by the metadata author. Example: Digitization of a photographic slide of a map would normally give the date at which the map was created; however a photographic work of art including the same map as its content may give the date of the original photographic exposure. Imprecise or unknown dates can be represented as ISO dates or ranges. Compare also Date and Time Digitized in the Resource Creation Vocabulary. See also the wikipedia IS0 8601 entry, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601, for further explanation and examples.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: Date on which the resource was changed.
skos:note: Date that the media resource was altered. The date and time MUST comply with the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) datetime practice, https://www.w3.org/TR/NOTE-datetime, which requires that date and time representation correspond to ISO 8601:1998, https://www.iso.org/standard/40874.html, but with year fields always comprising 4 digits. This makes datetime records compliant with 8601:2004. AC datetime values MAY also follow 8601:2004 for ranges by separating two IS0 8601 datetime fields by a solidus ("forward slash", '/'). dcterms:modified permits all modification dates to be recorded, or if only one is recorded, it is assumed to be the latest. See also the wikipedia IS0 8601 entry, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601, for further explanation and examples.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: A language of the content of Media.
skos:note: Recommended best prectice is to use an ISO639-2 three-letter language code.

dcterms:title: Media
skos:description: An account of the Media subject matter.
skos:note: Description of content of the resource, containing the Who, What, When, Where and Why as free-form text.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Occurrence.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make a dwc:occurrenceID globally unique.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAgentRole
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary for the roles appropriate to the class of resource an AgentRole is related to.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAgentRole
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAgentRole
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for agentRole is given.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAgentRole
skos:description: The numerical position of an AgentRole in a set of AgentRoles that have the same combination of agentRole, agentRoleIRI, agentRoleVocabulary and related target.
skos:note: One could use agentRoleOrder to create an ordered list of collectors (agentRole = 'collector') for a dwc:MaterialEntity, for example. The first would have agentRoleOrder=1, the second would have agentRoleOrder=2.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAgentRole
skos:description: The interval during which an AgentRole was in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Occurrence.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make a dwc:occurrenceID globally unique.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of an Assertion.
skos:example: `mass`; `mean mass`; `weight standard deviation`; `minimum organism quantity`; `water temperature`; `salinity`

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for assertionType is given.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: The date on which an Assertion was created.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: The date on which the state or measurement of an Assertion was deemed to first be in effect.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is not numeric.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the value of an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for assertionValue is given.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: An asserted value, if it is numeric.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: The units associated with the value in assertionValueNumeric.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Ontology of Units of Measure http://www.wurvoc.org/vocabularies/om-1.8/ of SI units, derived units, or other non-SI units accepted for use within the SI. For units that are composed of multiple parts, use the patterns as given in "A Primer for Communicating Mathematics via Plain Text" (https://cse.sc.edu/~fenner/latex-ASCII.pdf) by Stephen Fenner (e.g., `g/cm^3` for grams per cubic centimeter). For other units, provide the value as a recognizable standard (e.g., '%') or written out in full and in the plural (e.g., `individuals`). It is fine to provide non-SI units in the original language of the dataset.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: The IRI for the units of an assertionValueNumeric.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary in which the definition of the value in assertionUnit is given.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who made an Assertion.
skos:example: `José E. Crespo`; `Oliver P. Pearson | Anita K. Pearson`, `FMNH`

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent who made an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.
skos:example: `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097` (for an individual); `https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097 | https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0098` (for a list of people)

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: The names of, references to, or descriptions of the methods or protocols used in making an Assertion.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: An identifier for a Protocol used to make an Assertion.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with an Assertion.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/322/5899/261`; `Christopher J. Conroy, Jennifer L. Neuwald. 2008. Phylogeographic study of the California vole, Microtus californicus Journal of Mammalogy, 89(3):755-767.`; `Steven R. Hoofer and Ronald A. Van Den Bussche. 2001. Phylogenetic Relationships of Plecotine Bats and Allies Based on Mitochondrial Ribosomal Sequences. Journal of Mammalogy 82(1):131-137. | Walker, Faith M., Jeffrey T. Foster, Kevin P. Drees, Carol L. Chambers. 2014. Spotted bat (Euderma maculatum) microsatellite discovery using illumina sequencing. Conservation Genetics Resources.`

dcterms:title: OccurrenceAssertion
skos:description: Comments or notes about an Assertion.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: An identifier for a Citation.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Occurrence.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make a dwc:occurrenceID globally unique.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a Citation.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Citation.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for citationType is given.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: A bibliographic reference for the resource.
skos:note: From Dublin Core, 'Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.' The intended usage of this term in Darwin Core is to provide the preferred way to cite the resource itself. Note that the intended usage of dcterms:references in Darwin Core, by contrast, is to point to the definitive source representation of the resource, if one is available.
skos:example: `Museum of Vertebrate Zoology, UC Berkeley. MVZ Mammal Collection (Arctos). Record ID: http://arctos.database.museum/guid/MVZ:Mamm:165861?seid=101356. Source: http://ipt.vertnet.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=mvz_mammal.` (Occurrence example); `https://www.gbif.org/species/2439608 Source: GBIF Taxonomic Backbone` (Taxon example); `Rand, K.M., Logerwell, E.A. The first demersal trawl survey of benthic fish and invertebrates in the Beaufort Sea since the late 1970s. Polar Biol 34, 475–488 (2011). https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-010-0900-2` (Event example)

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: The number of the page on which the citation occurs in the cited reference.
skos:note: From Dublin Core, 'Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.' The intended usage of this term in Darwin Core is to provide the preferred way to cite the resource itself. Note that the intended usage of dcterms:references in Darwin Core, by contrast, is to point to the definitive source representation of the resource, if one is available.
skos:example: `Museum of Vertebrate Zoology, UC Berkeley. MVZ Mammal Collection (Arctos). Record ID: http://arctos.database.museum/guid/MVZ:Mamm:165861?seid=101356. Source: http://ipt.vertnet.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=mvz_mammal.` (Occurrence example); `https://www.gbif.org/species/2439608 Source: GBIF Taxonomic Backbone` (Taxon example); `Rand, K.M., Logerwell, E.A. The first demersal trawl survey of benthic fish and invertebrates in the Beaufort Sea since the late 1970s. Polar Biol 34, 475–488 (2011). https://doi.org/10.1007/s00300-010-0900-2` (Event example)

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: An identifier for the reference in which a Citation occurs.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a reference.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of reference.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for referenceType is given.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: The year the reference in a Citation was published.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: An indication of whether the reference for a Citation was peer reviewed.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceCitation
skos:description: Comments or notes about a Citation.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceIdentifier
skos:description: An unambiguous reference to a resource within a given context.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to identify a resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceIdentifier
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Occurrence.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make a dwc:occurrenceID globally unique.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceIdentifier
skos:description: The category or system that best matches the nature of an Identifier.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceIdentifier
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the type of Identifier.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceIdentifier
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for identifierType is given.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceIdentifier
skos:description: A language in which an Identifier is presented.
skos:note: Recommended best prectice is to use an ISO639-2 three-letter language code.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceMedia
skos:description: An identifier for a Media instance.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceMedia
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Occurrence.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make a dwc:occurrenceID globally unique.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceMedia
skos:description: A term to describe the content of the image by a value from a controlled vocabulary.
skos:note: Controlled vocabulary of subjects to support broad classification of media items. Terms from various controlled vocabularies may be used. AC-recommended vocabularies are preferred and MAY be unqualified literals (not a full URI). For terms from other vocabularies either a precise URI SHOULD be used, or, as long as all unqualified terms in all vocabularies are unique, metadata SHOULD provide the source vocabularies using the Subject Category Vocabulary term. The value SHOULD be a string, whose text can also be in the form of a URL. These guidelines on value format are less restrictive than is specified by the IPTC guidelines.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceMedia
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the subject category of the Media instance.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceMedia
skos:description: Any vocabulary or formal classification from which terms in the Subject Category have been drawn.
skos:note: The AC recommended vocabularies do not need to be cited here. There is no required linkage between individual Subject Category terms and the vocabulary; the mechanism is intended to support discovery of the normative URI for a term, but not guarantee it.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceProtocol
skos:description: An identifier for a Protocol.

dcterms:title: OccurrenceProtocol
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Occurrence.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make a dwc:occurrenceID globally unique.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Occurrence.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a persistent, globally unique identifier. In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make a dwc:occurrenceID globally unique.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Event.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: An identifier for a SurveyTarget.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations responsible for recording a dwc:Occurrence.
skos:example: `José E. Crespo`; `Oliver P. Pearson | Anita K. Pearson`, `FMNH`

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: An identifier for the Agent responsible for recording a dwc:Occurrence.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A number or enumeration value for the quantity of dwc:Organisms.
skos:note: A dwc:organismQuantity must have a corresponding dwc:organismQuantityType.
skos:example: `27` (organismQuantity) with `individuals` (organismQuantityType); `12.5` (organismQuantity) with `% biomass` (organismQuantityType); `r` (organismQuantity) with `Braun-Blanquet Scale` (organismQuantityType); `many` (organismQuantity) with `individuals` (organismQuantityType)

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A type of quantification system used for the quantity of dwc:Organisms.
skos:note: A dwc:organismQuantityType must have a corresponding dwc:organismQuantity. This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.
skos:example: `27` (organismQuantity) with `individuals` (organismQuantityType); `12.5` (organismQuantity) with `% biomass` (organismQuantityType); `r` (organismQuantity) with `Braun-Blanquet Scale` (organismQuantityType); `many` (organismQuantity) with `individuals` (organismQuantityType)

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for an organism quantity type.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for dwc:organismQuantityType is given.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The sex of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The age class or life stage of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The reproductive condition a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The social caste of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary that aligns best with a dwc:Taxon. This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The behavior shown by a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: An indication of whether a dwc:Organism was alive or dead at the time of collection or observation.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Intended to be used with records having a dwc:basisOfRecord of PreservedSpecimen, MaterialEntity, MaterialSample, or HumanObservation. This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: Statement about whether a dwc:Organism has been introduced to a given place and time through the direct or indirect activity of modern humans.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use controlled value strings from the controlled vocabulary designated for use with this term, listed at http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/doc/em/. For details, refer to https://doi.org/10.3897/biss.3.38084. This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The degree to which a dwc:Organism survives, reproduces, and expands its range at a given place and time.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use controlled value strings from the controlled vocabulary designated for use with this term, listed at http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/doc/doe/. For details, refer to https://doi.org/10.3897/biss.3.38084. This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The process by which a dwc:Organism came to be in a given place at a given time.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use controlled value strings from the controlled vocabulary designated for use with this term, listed at http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/doc/pw/. For details, refer to https://doi.org/10.3897/biss.3.38084. This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A statement about the presence or absence of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: For dwc:Occurrences, the default vocabulary is recommended to consist of present and absent, but can be extended by implementers with good justification. This term has an equivalent in the dwciri: namespace that allows only an IRI as a value, whereas this term allows for any string literal value.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with a dwc:Occurrence.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `Christopher J. Conroy, Jennifer L. Neuwald. 2008. Phylogeographic study of the California vole, Microtus californicus Journal of Mammalogy, 89(3):755-767.`; `Steven R. Hoofer and Ronald A. Van Den Bussche. 2001. Phylogenetic Relationships of Plecotine Bats and Allies Based on Mitochondrial Ribosomal Sequences. Journal of Mammalogy 82(1):131-137. | Walker, Faith M., Jeffrey T. Foster, Kevin P. Drees, Carol L. Chambers. 2014. Spotted bat (Euderma maculatum) microsatellite discovery using illumina sequencing. Conservation Genetics Resources.`

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: Additional information that exists, but that has not been shared in the given record.
skos:example: `location information not given for endangered species`; `collector identities withheld | ask about tissue samples`

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: Actions taken to make the shared data less specific or complete than in its original form. Suggests that alternative data of higher quality may be available on request.
skos:example: `coordinates generalized from original GPS coordinates to the nearest half degree grid cell`

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dwc:Occurrence.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Organism.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A description of the type of dwc:Organism instance.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Can be used to indicate whether a dwc:Organism instance represents a discrete organism or if it represents a particular type of aggregation.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for an organism scope.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for dwc:organismScope is given.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A name or label assigned to a dwc:Organism.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dwc:Organism.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A string representing the taxonomic identification as it appeared in the original record.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A string representing the pattern to use to construct a dwc:Identification from dwc:Taxon names and identification qualifiers.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as https://arctos.database.museum/info/ctDocumentation.cfm?table=cttaxa_formula.
skos:example: `A`; `A ?`; `A or B`; `A and B`; `A x B`; `A cf.`; `A aff.`

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who made a taxonomic determination of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The identifier for the Agent who made a taxonomic determination of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to provide a single identifier that disambiguates the details of the identifying agent. If a list is used, the order of the identifiers on the list should not be assumed to convey any semantics. Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who made a taxonomic determination of a dwc:Organism.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601-1:2019.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A list (concatenated and separated) of references (publication, global unique identifier, URI) used in a dwc:Identification.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to separate the values in a list with space vertical bar space (` | `).
skos:example: `Aves del Noroeste Patagonico. Christie et al. 2004.`; `Stebbins, R. Field Guide to Western Reptiles and Amphibians. 3rd Edition. 2003. | Irschick, D.J. and Shaffer, H.B. (1997). The polytypic species revisited: Morphological differentiation among tiger salamanders (Ambystoma tigrinum) (Amphibia: Caudata). Herpetologica, 53(1), 30-49.`

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: A categorical indicator of the extent to which the taxonomic determination has been verified to be correct.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as that used in HISPID and ABCD.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for an identification verification.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for dwc:identificationVerificationStatus is given.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dwc:Identification.
skos:example: `Distinguished between Anthus correndera and Anthus hellmayri based on the comparative lengths of the uñas.`

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: An identifier for a dwc:Taxon.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The full scientific name of the kingdom in which a dwc:scientificName is classified.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The full scientific name, with authorship and date information if known. When forming part of a dwc:Identification, this should be the name in lowest level taxonomic rank that can be determined. This term should not contain identification qualifications, which should instead be supplied in dwc:verbatimIdentification.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: The taxonomic rank of the most specific name in a dwc:scientificName.

dcterms:title: Occurrence
skos:description: Comments or notes about a dwc:Taxon.
skos:example: `this name is a misspelling in common use`

dcterms:title: OrganismInteractionAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a globally unique identifier.

dcterms:title: OrganismInteractionAgentRole
skos:description: An identifier for an OrganismInteraction.

dcterms:title: OrganismInteractionAgentRole
skos:description: The category that best matches the nature of a role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary for the roles appropriate to the class of resource an AgentRole is related to.

dcterms:title: OrganismInteractionAgentRole
skos:description: The IRI of the controlled vocabulary value for the role of an Agent.
skos:note: Recommended best practice is to use an IRI for a term in a controlled vocabulary.

dcterms:title: OrganismInteractionAgentRole
skos:description: The reference to the controlled vocabulary where the definition of the value for agentRole is given.

dcterms:title: OrganismInteractionAgentRole
skos:description: The numerical position of an AgentRole in a set of AgentRoles that have the same combination of agentRole, agentRoleIRI, agentRoleVocabulary and related target.
